Morale’s belligerent rhetoric has blunted any remaining good intentions of Chile, he suggested.
Bolivia and Chile will continue negotiations at some point, but it will be very difficult to maintain discussions in the wake of what has happened.
The two countries have not exchanged ambassadors since 1962.
