On Monday, Bolivia will be able to “enjoy extraordinary opportunities in relations with Chile” and will have the opportunity to “end 139 years of disagreements with mutual benefit,” he explained.
Calzadilla also denied that Morales – one of Latin America’s most popular presidents – is using the maritime issue as political swindle.
